The paper deals with visual recognition and localization using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves an iterative scheme that alternates between classification and introspection, which is a form of active learning and could be considered a form of reinforcement learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its method on several datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
